{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1666339439,"nonce":"38Z9AmbYjwpljCAN5pM99iPk+88=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5MsBt3","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4851#issuecomment-1286609783"},"message":"@gallardoalba in the failed unicycler run in that test history the inputs are in `fastq.gz` format when the tool only allows `fastqsanger` and `fastqsanger.gz`.\nThe problem is that the wrapper checks only the cases `is_of_type('fastqsanger')` and `is_of_type('fastqsanger.gz')`, but doesn't set any variables for other cases.\n\nSo if you're forcing the tool to work on general fastq data (how does that work btw? can you just drag and drop such datasets into the input boxes?) you're currently out of luck. A possible improvement over this current situation (beyond teaching users to set the correct datatype) would be to change the `is_of_type` checks to more general `.ext.endswith('.gz') ones.","files":null}]}